data.title: GoDaddy.com to debut new Pussycat Dolls lineup during Super Bowl Ads 2012 (watch video)
data.meta_description: Watch the video of the new Pussycat Dolls line up as part of GoDaddy.com's Super Bowl Ads 2012.
data.text:
Pussycat Dolls creator Robin Antin has announced five new singers who will make their debut during the Super Bowl Ads 2012 for GoDaddy.com.

The all-girl group will feature:

• Lauren Bennett from Paradiso Girls,

• Vanessa Curry of the Laker Girls,

• Erica Jenkins of the Dallas Cowboy cheerleaders,

• Chrystina Sayers from Girlicious

• and Paula Van Oppen of "So You Think You Can Dance."

The new Pussycat Dolls ad during Super Bowl XLVI (Sunday, NBC) is "breathtakingly beautiful. It's a fun, real campy kind of sexy," Antin told MTV.

In the spot, the girls are on the Go Daddy cloud. "They're angels in heaven, and they're very angelic," she added.

The new women replace original members Nicole Scherzinger, Melody Thornton, Ashley Roberts, Jessica Sutta and Kimberly Wyatt. Carmit Bachar left the group in 2008, according to US Magazine.
